<td colspan="3"><b>Additional notes:</b>
<ul>
<li>Guidance on making articles conform to the neutrality policy can be found at <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Neutral_point_of_view/FAQ" title="Wikipedia:Neutral point of view/FAQ">Wikipedia:Neutral point of view/FAQ</a>. For a list of articles that have been marked as potentially containing a NPOV problem, see <a href="/wiki/Category:NPOV_disputes" title="Category:NPOV disputes">Category:NPOV disputes</a></li>
<li>If your question is about whether material constitutes <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:NOR" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:NOR">original research</a>, use the <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:No_original_research/noticeboard" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:No original research/noticeboard">No original research noticeboard</a> instead. For a review of whether a source is <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Reliable_sources" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:Reliable sources">reliable</a>, go to the <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Reliable_sources/Noticeboard" title="Wikipedia:Reliable sources/Noticeboard">Reliable sources noticeboard</a>.</li>
<li>If you are satisfied with a response, please tag your thread at the top with {{<a href="/wiki/Template:Resolved" title="Template:Resolved">resolved</a>}}.</li>
<li>See also <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Countering_systemic_bias" title="Wikipedia:WikiProject Countering systemic bias">Wikipedia:WikiProject Countering systemic bias</a>.</li>
